# Local-only AI toolchain & planning — never tracked in this (public-bound) repo.
# BMad install + Claude config live here untracked; planning/implementation
# artifacts live in the private sibling repo github.com/mlmeehan/tesla-card-planning.
/_bmad/
/.claude/
/_bmad-output/

# BMAD / planning artifact FILENAMES — advisory first layer so a stray planning doc
# written outside the dirs above (into docs/, root, …) isn't accidentally `git add`ed.
# The hard, source-of-truth enforcement is scripts/lint/no-planning-artifacts.mjs
# (npm run lint + the native pre-commit hook + the Claude Bash guard). The doc-project
# outputs we DO publish (docs/architecture.md, source-tree-analysis.md,
# component-inventory.md, layer-contract.md, audit-r6-*.md) are NOT matched here.
prd.md
prd-*.md
prd_*.md
epic.md
epics.md
epic-*.md
epics-*.md
story-*.md
*.story.md
spec-*.md
ux-*.md
brief-*.md
sprint-status*.md
sprint-status*.yaml
sprint-status*.yml
sprint-plan*.md
sprint-change*.md
correct-course*.md
retrospective*.md
retro-*.md
brainstorming-*.md
product-brief*.md
prfaq*.md
pr-faq*.md
market-research*.md
domain-research*.md
technical-research*.md
traceability-matrix*.md
test-design*.md
test-review*.md
nfr-assessment*.md
implementation-readiness*.md
project-context.md
# (numeric story files like 5-10-media-panel.md / 8.12.md are enforced by the gate,
#  not gitignored, to avoid silently hiding a date-named doc like 2026-06-20-notes.md)

# Local-only recolor test art (bring-your-own; Tesla trade-dress stays out of the repo)
demo/local/

# Tesla trade-dress source art — never commit/redistribute Tesla renders or vectorizations
# of them (CLAUDE.md [card]: "No vehicle artwork ships — bring your own"). These are the
# source Tesla Model Y renders, the tracing workshop, and the photo-traced SVGs/docs derived
# from them. Generic bring-your-own recolor sources can be re-included later if needed.
docs/Tesla1.png
docs/Tesla2.png
docs/tesla1-svg/
assets/

# Transient probes planted by the co-located gate tests (import-allowlist,
# no-network-egress, no-bare-hass-states, no-cycle) to exercise the real gates
# (normally removed in a finally; this guards against a hard-killed run leaving one
# behind).
src/__import_allowlist_probe__.ts
src/__no_network_egress_probe__.ts
src/__no_bare_hass_probe__.ts
src/__no_cycle_probe_a__.ts
src/__no_cycle_probe_b__.ts

# Playwright E2E artifacts (reports/results are regenerated; baselines under
# tests/**/-snapshots/ ARE committed and must not be ignored)
/test-results/
/playwright-report/
/playwright/.cache/
/blob-report/

# NFR-1 FPS profiler run artifacts (fps-results.json + scene screenshot) — the
# harness (scripts/profiler/) IS tracked; its per-run output is regenerated.
/scripts/profiler/out/
.claude/.story-automator-active
